P(A \cup B \cup C) = P(A) + P(B) + P(C) - P(A \cap B) - P(B \cap C) - P(A \cap C) + P(A \cap B \cap C)
P(A \cup B \cup C) = P(A \cup B) \cup C
P(A \cup B \cup C) = P((A \cup B) \cup C) \\=P(A \cup B) +P( C)-P((A \cup B) \cap C) \\=P(A )+P(B)-P(A \cap B) +P( C)-P((A\cap C) \cup (B \cap C) \\ =P(A) + P(B) + P(C) - P(A \cap B) - P(B \cap C) - P(A \cap C) + P(A \cap B \cap C)
